"I'm hiring a freelance product designer for a full product redesign. My budget ceiling is $95/hr but I've told the other side we can do $80/hr — I'd rather stay at $85 if possible. My last two contract designers quit mid-project so I desperately need someone reliable who'll finish. My VP wants the redesign shipped by end of Q2 (14 weeks away) and if we don't start in two weeks the timeline is dead. I would consider a longer engagement (6 months instead of 3) if that brought the rate down, since we have a design backlog after the redesign. I think the freelancer is talented and don't want to lowball him out of the deal."
